The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Robbers in taxi held
                                                                                                               Robbers in taxi held
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Two youths who robbed a taxi driver, threw him out of the vehicle and then used it to rob two pedestrians were arrested on Monday.         
	Mohammad Kasif Sahim and Mohammad Shahnawaz were traced to a hideout at Mallikpur in South 24-Parganas. A firearm was found in their possession.        
	The duo hired the taxi at Panchannagram in South 24-Parganas on April 8 night. They overpowered the driver and snatched Rs 1,600 and a cellphone from him as the vehicle reached Entally. The two then pushed the driver out of the vehicle at Park Circus crossing, said police.        
	The duo then drove to Topsia, dragged a pedestrian into the taxi, robbed him at gunpoint and dumped him on the EM Bypass. They did the same to another pedestrian standing at the Narkeldanga crossing before abandoning the taxi near Bridge No. 4.                                                                                                                                                                            
